# Auth and Session Rules

## Scope
- Auth logic lives in `apps/api/controllers/auth.controller.ts` and `apps/api/routes/auth.routes.ts`.
- Session typing is declared in `apps/api/global.d.ts`.

## Session Contract
- Session fields currently used: `isLoggedIn?: boolean`, `user?: User`.
- Add any new session fields to `apps/api/global.d.ts`, not ad hoc in controllers.
- After changing session state (login/signup), call `req.session.save()` before redirect.

## Auth Route Surface
- `GET /login`, `POST /login`
- `GET /logout`
- `GET /signup`, `POST /signup`
- `GET /reset`, `POST /reset`
- `GET /reset-password`, `POST /reset-password`

## Controller Flow Expectations
- `postLogin`: validate request, compare password hash with `bcrypt.compareSync`, set session, redirect to `/admin/products`.
- `postSignup`: validate fields, prevent duplicate email, hash password, create user, set session, redirect, send welcome email.
- `postReset`: validate email, create reset JWT via `NodeMailModel`, persist token via `TokenModel`, send reset link email.
- `getResetPassword`: verify token and render reset-password page with `_email` and `_token`.
- `postResetPassword`: update hashed password and delete used token record.
- `getLogout`: destroy session and redirect to `/`.

## Flash Message Contract
- Errors: `req.flash('error', ...)`
- Success: `req.flash('success', ...)`
- Views consume values from `res.locals.error` and `res.locals.success`.

## Middleware Assumptions
- `req.user` is hydrated globally in `apps/api/app.ts` from `req.session.user`.
- Do not duplicate user hydration in auth controllers.
- `res.locals.userName` is set globally and used in navigation.

## Do Not
- Do not store raw passwords.
- Do not bypass `req.session.save()` before redirects after session mutation.
- Do not expose admin handlers outside `/admin` + `isAuth` guarded route mount.
